3 Expression specificity

zones <- c(rep("A",3),rep("B",3),rep("C",3),
           rep("A",3),rep("B",3),rep("C",6),
           rep("A",3),rep("B",3),rep("C",6))
exp.spec <- expressionSpecificity(caz.dat,zones,"local","complete")
## Calculating tissue specificity

Sort by expression peak and tissue specificity

exp.peak <- c("A","B","C")[apply(exp.spec[,c("A","B","C")] == exp.spec[,"maxn"],1,which)]
ord <- order(exp.peak,(1-exp.spec[,"score"]))

Export

write.csv(cbind(exp.spec,exp.peak)[ord,],file="cazymes_immanen-vst-expression-data_expression-specificity-order.csv")

5 Tissue specific Heatmaps

Extract the blocks using the tissue spec. Then perform the correlation clustering on the 4 tissues.

dev.null <- sapply(levels(factor(exp.peak)),function(tissue,tlist,zones,dat){
  sel <- tlist == tissue
  hc <- hclust(pearson.dist(dat[sel,]),method = "ward.D")
  plot(hc,labels=FALSE)
  heatmap.2(dat[sel,],col=hpal,Colv=FALSE,
            distfun=pearson.dist,
            hclustfun=function(d){hclust(d,method = "ward.D")},
            dendrogram="row",trace="none",labRow = FALSE,
            ColSideColors = pal[as.integer(factor(zones))],
            labCol = samples$othernames)
  
  pdf(file = paste0("cazymes-tissue-",tissue,"-heatmap.pdf"),width=7, height=42)
  heatmap.2(dat[sel,][hc$order,],col=hpal,Colv=FALSE,Rowv=FALSE,
            dendrogram="none",trace="none",labRow = 1:sum(sel),
            ColSideColors = pal[as.integer(factor(zones))],
            key = FALSE,labCol = samples$othernames)
  dev.off()
  
  pdf(file = paste0("cazymes-tissue-",tissue,"-dendrogram.pdf"),width=42, height=7)
  plot(hc)
  dev.off()
  
  write.csv(cbind(data.frame(geneID=hc$labels[hc$order],pos=1:sum(sel)),
                  t(scale(t(dat[hc$order,])))),
            file=paste0("cazymes-tissue-",tissue,"-heatmap.csv"))
  
},exp.peak[hc$order][sel],zones,s.caz.dat[hc$order,][sel,])
